Reason: expected 'true' in CORS header 'Access-Control-Allow-Credentials'

<L=c#4>Reason</L><I=4>
    Reason: expected 'true' in CORS header 'Access-Control-Allow-Credentials'

<L=c#5>What went wrong?</L><I=5>
The CORS request requires that the server permit the use of credentials, but the server's
<L=S> Access-Control-Allow-Credentials </L> header's value isn't set to  true  to enable their use.

To fix this problem on the client side, revise the code to not request the use of credentials.

-   If using the Fetch API , make sure  Request.credentials  is  "omit"  .
-   If the request is being issued using  XMLHttpRequest  , make sure you're not setting
     withCredentials  to  true  .
-   If using Server-sent events , make sure  EventSource.withCredentials  is  false  (it's the default
    value).

To eliminate this error by changing the server's configuration, adjust the server's configuration to set
the  Access-Control-Allow-Credentials  header's value to  true  .

