Reason: CORS header 'Origin' cannot be added

<L=i#4>Reason</L><I=4>
    Reason: CORS header 'Origin' cannot be added

<L=i#5>What went wrong?</L><I=5>
The user agent was unable to add the required <L=2m> Origin </L> header to the HTTP request. All CORS
requests must have an  Origin  header.

This can happen if the JavaScript code is running with enhanced privileges allowing it access to multiple
domains' content, for example.

<L=i#6>See also</L><I=6>
-   <L=5>CORS errors</L>
-   Glossary: CORS
-   <L=4>CORS introduction</L>
