Allow

The HTTP  Allow  response header lists the set of <L=4l>request methods</L> supported by a resource. This
header must be sent if the server responds with a <L=4X> 405 Method Not Allowed </L> status code to
indicate which request methods can be used instead. An empty  Allow  value indicates that the resource
allows no request methods, which might occur temporarily for a given resource.

  -------------------------- -----------------
  Header type                Response header
  Forbidden request header   No
  -------------------------- -----------------

<L=11#4>Syntax</L><I=4>
http

    Allow: <http-methods>

<L=11#5>Directives</L><I=5>
 <http-methods> 

    A comma-separated list of allowed request methods supported by a resource.

<L=11#6>Examples</L><I=6>
http

    Allow: GET, POST, HEAD

<L=11#7>Specifications</L><I=7>
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Specification
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  HTTP Semantics
  # field.allow

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<L=11#8>See also</L><I=8>
