The HTTP <L=1k> Content-Security-Policy </L> (CSP)  media-src  directive specifies valid sources for
loading media using the  <audio>  and  <video>  elements.

  ---------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  CSP version                        1
  Directive type                     Fetch directive
  <L=1q> default-src </L> fallback   Yes. If this directive is absent, the user agent will look for the  default-src  directive.
