The HTTP <L=2o> Permissions-Policy </L> header  hid  directive controls whether the current document is
allowed to use the WebHID API to connect to uncommon or exotic human interface devices such as
alternative keyboards or gamepads.

Specifically, where a defined policy blocks WebHID usage, the  Navigator.hid  property will not be
available.

