The HTTP <L=2o> Permissions-Policy </L> header  serial  directive controls whether the current document
is allowed to use the Web Serial API to communicate with serial devices, either directly connected via a
serial port, or via USB or Bluetooth devices emulating a serial port.

Specifically, where a defined policy blocks use of this feature,  Serial.requestPort()  and
 Serial.getPorts()  calls will return a  Promise  that rejects with a  DOMException  of type
 SecurityError  .

<L=2U#4>Syntax</L><I=4>
http

    Permissions-Policy: serial=<allowlist>;

 <allowlist> 

    A list of origins for which permission is granted to use the feature. See
    <L=2o#4> Permissions-Policy  > Syntax</L> for more details.

<L=2U#5>Default policy</L><I=5>
The default allowlist for  serial  is  self  .

<L=2U#6>Specifications</L><I=6>
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Specification
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
