424 Failed Dependency

The HTTP  424 Failed Dependency  <L=4w#7>client error response</L> status code indicates that the method
could not be performed on the resource because the requested action depended on another action, and that
action failed.

Regular web servers typically do not return this status code, but some protocols like WebDAV can return
it. For example, in WebDAV , if a  PROPPATCH  request was issued, and one command fails then
automatically every other command will also fail with  424 Failed Dependency  .

<L=5e#4>Status</L><I=4>
http

    424 Failed Dependency

<L=5e#5>Specifications</L><I=5>
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Specification
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  RFC 4918
  # section-11.4

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

